We have both hands in favor of this announcement. ”
Ian Green, chief executive of Terence Higgins Trust, said: “The first priority now is to ensure that the trial is pushed quickly across the country, and that none of the people living with HIV can fall behind.
Now that we have purchased PrEP trial drugs, we are ready to protect more than 10,000 people at high risk of HIV. ”
Shadow Public Health Minister Sharon Hodgson claimed: "After months of delay and the delay of the government, PrEP's initial trial work was popular and should have arrived sooner.
The evidence suggests how this drug can bring about as part of our approach to preventing HIV and halting the spread of this deadly infectious disease.
