With the recent announcement of the construction plan of the new frigates by the world's major naval powers, as if the frigates have become the focus of the Navy's focus overnight, first Japan in the 2018 defense budget to determine the procurement of two new frigates, so that the Japanese DEX frigate plan finally has a substantial breakthrough, and then the United States Lockheed Martin recently announced the latest plan of the United States FFG frigate, so where should China's new frigates go?
With the launch of a new frigate of the new Type 054A frigate at the end of 2017, the 50A frigate has been built up to 29, which has been close to the sum of the 053H series of frigates, and the construction of the 054A has been launched from the first 054A in 2006 to the 12th year, even in the world, such a large number of high-performance universal frigates, in addition to China, only the United States in the 7th and 1980s "Peri" class frigates can be compared.
And the reason why so many R054As is built is that it is affordable, easy to use, and add years of Navy debt.
054A frigate with a high cost-effective and good combat effectiveness for many years has been favored by the Chinese Navy, its 4000 tons of drainage, equipped with a 76mm main gun, 32 unit sea flag-16 and fish-8 anti-submarine missile co-launched vertical system, eight eagle 83 and a straight-9 helicopter, although it is 2006 began to build, the design time is a very early type of ship, but its combat effectiveness is not too bad today, the world's frigates can also reach the level.
But after all, this is a type of first-stage 21st century design of the ship, the weapon configuration on the side, its power system and electronic radar equipment and the current world's mainstream frigates already have a big gap, like Europe's same type of frigate has been equipped with full-electric propulsion, small multi-functional phased array radar, large-size helicopter deck, the time to develop new models.
Then it is directly related to how China's new frigates should be developed, which has a direct relationship with its future positioning and our strategic approach to the Chinese Navy.
The future development of the Chinese Navy will be completely become a blue-water navy, and the future will also be the ocean, with China's vital interests closely related to the region for rapid deployment, show the existence of force, if necessary, can have a strong combat effectiveness to ensure that China's vital interests in the region are not damaged, so it seems that the new Hu Weijiang will be towards large-scale, oceanization development.
Looking at the positioning of the new frigates in the future Chinese Navy sequence, the future Chinese Navy should be similar to the US Navy, in addition to the necessary offshore defense ships, other main ships will be necessary to form a carrier strike group or amphibious assault ship strike group according to the situation.
The role of the new frigates in the future aircraft carrier battle group should act as a position of anti-submarine main force and near-regional release, and should act as a escort ship in the amphibious assault ship strike group, so according to such needs, the new frigates must have a strong anti-submarine capability and a good intermediate-range regional air release capability.
Based on the above positioning, you can boldly imagine the future of the domestic frigates' approximate appearance.
