The report was interviewed by “millennials ” young people in nine countries (born between 1980 and 2000).
According to the report, China's post-80s and post-90s high-level housing ownership rate for young people as high as 70%, far ahead of second-place Mexico (46%), which is also the two-fold level of the United States indicator (35%).
These data tell us a highly likely problem, which is that Chinese residents' biggest potential "gray rhinos" at this stage, compared to the inability to afford a home, it is estimated that Chinese residents will not be able to pay off debt.
Why is the housing debt crisis the most serious problem?
As we have previously analyzed, although we have been saying that China's house prices are higher, compared with other countries in the world, China's housing ownership rate is actually quite high, so it is not so much that house prices can't afford to buy a house, I'm afraid to ask a lot of friends now is the question of whether you can afford a loan?
We look at the real estate market in the world, China's real estate market has started late, in addition to what we said Hainan, there has not been a major real estate crisis, but just a decade ago, the origin of the global financial tsunami in 2008 is the real estate crisis in the United States.
And the cause of the U.S. real estate crisis has been blamed on two homes: Fannie Mae and Freddie.
At that time, in the golden age of the United States, real estate companies sold their houses to low-income people in the United States in order to expand sales, and when the U.S. economy was good, the real estate market was also thriving, but the sky was not long, and with the stagnation of growth in the U.S. economy, it caused the income of homebuyers to decline, so a large amount of household consumption expenditure began to decline.
However, at that time, the current situation in the United States was a component of financial assets and real estate assets of household assets in the United States, and almost all households in the United States were real estate, and most of the assets of the top 20% of the high-income group were financial assets, so the higher the debt ratio of real estate in the United States.
A serious fact is that these people are in the economy when they buy a house, so the money to pay mortgages is also calculated by their better income, when the income declines, the pressure of mortgages not only has not decreased or even because some subprime plans have become floating, so the real estate problems of these American families have gradually evolved into a real estate crisis.
So some people because the income is too low to pay the mortgage, so the bank began to recover the property, when the bank from the loan home buyers after the property, they will be sold at a very low price, resulting in a gradual decline in the house price, the process has triggered a further decline in house prices, the formation of a vicious circle, when the house price fell to a certain extent, more and more buyers found that the value of their house is even lower than their own loans, so there are more people to stop repaying the mortgage, resulting in more bad debts.
Thus, a huge vicious circle is formed:
“The economy is in a slump, income declines as a part of the people can ’ t afford the mortgages Bank selling the houses of the under-age people at a low price? ’ s house rates, the house bill falls?
And the problem is not so, because the house price continues to fall, we stop repaying the house to the bank after you do not have debt, if the bank auction house to get the money you can not owe the bank's loan, then you still need to pay back money, simply say that you use the down payment of 600,000, loan 240 million to buy a set of 3 million houses worth at that time, when the house fell to the house worth only two million, you no longer loan to the bank, after the bank auction house, you not only lost their own down payment.
As a result, in this vicious circle after another, the US economy gradually collapsed, which eventually triggered the financial crisis of the United States in 2008.
Therefore, at this stage, the level of China's household debt rate to a high of 46.8% is a very need to be a very vigilant issue, this data is still lower than the level of developed countries, but the problem has begun to appear, the country has repeatedly stressed the deleveraging problem since last year, which is a very insightful judgment, if the family debt rate is allowed to continue to climb, it will inevitably lead to huge risks, so to strictly prevent the emergence of financial risks.
As a result, with the location of the house used for living, not for speculation, the country has accelerated the establishment of multiple measures such as multi-subject supply, multi-channel guarantee, rent and purchase, and further resolve potential risks.
For our personal families, we must give up the speculative thinking of real estate, buy a house when doing their best, to avoid their own family into a huge burden, only a reasonable assessment of their income and debt level is a healthy family wealth development path.
